rComments: Great lecturer.
he's really approachable

GREAT PROF! He's very enthusiastic about the topics he teaches and answers all questions posed by students no matter how irrelevant they may be. I would definetely take another course with him. And he is really cute too (bonus!)
A total turkey, full of himself and fully convinced of his own intelligence.
Omg i love him! so cute! love the way he dresses, looks and talks!!! <3
Wonderful Prof
Went to the first class then dropped the course. Could not stand to listen to this guy for 3 hours a week. Very full of himself, high expectations. Think he may have modeled for a Zellers flyer.

This prof is wonderful. I only wish that I could've taken more courses with him. A bit of a warning: be prepared to work and to write quickly. If you can do those two things, you'll have no problems. And, if ever you need help, this prof is always willing to help (though not to give you the answer).

This professor is a stinker.  He knows his stuff, but he is a horrible "teacher".  He is no doubt an expert, but not a teacher.  He is an atrociously hard marker and expects way too much of his students.  The assignments are spaced out well and relate to course material really well, but his DGDs are just for nitpicking TAs, not "discussion".
Great Prof. He is so passionate about the subject and makes the class very interesting. Make sure to attend EVERY class!

good prof. he knows his stuff and is very clear!! you can tell he is passionate about the content, which makes the course more interesting. only downside to the class is the lack of DGD's.. but the course is very well structured. HIGHLY recommended. workload is relatively light, but attending lectures are an absolute must.
he is a great professor. the only class i actually look forward to. very intresting and thought provoking plus he's SO damn cute!
he is a great prof.
Great Prof. If you go and pay attention (and of course like political theory) this is an amazing class. I have found it to be fairly marked as well - just dont expect an easy course. Recommended.
I love this prof: very intelligent, very interesting, one of the best teachers at Ottawa U. Don't miss a chance to take this course.

Interesting material eventhough the lectures often feel way too long. Covers alot of material with little readings so it is important to attend lectures. Marking is fair as long as you put in the work.
love the metrosexuals

Prof. Breaugh has high expectations and it's too bad some of his more negative students skipped too many high school classes. Talk about not being prepared for Pstsecondary studies!!! His expectations are high; that's great for the money I'm dishing out in tuition.

His exam was easy, but he is a disturbingly hard marker and expects us to be at his PHD level. He didn't take any blame for the outcome of the exam (the average was 54%). I am 100% sure that he is out to screw us over.
his exams are hard

Prof. Breaugh has a lot to say but the man is definitely worth listening to. You have to be able to accept his intellectual challenge to appreciate his teaching capacity. I look forward to hearing more of his lectures in the future.
he doesn't know how to say something in one sentence, this prof spits out needless detail just to take up class time as far as i'm concerned. although he is very intelligent
This professor is in love with himself and only teaches as an ego-boost
No Comments

Breaugh is young and eloquent. Dont let age fool you, his lectures are thoughtful and clever in the way they are designed to make you think for yourself. You have to trick him into answering your big questions about texts because he wont just tell you.

as political science profs go, he's pretty damn good. he does a good job chalenging and pushing your limits but still has remained interesting to me. I look forward to the class. can't think of anything bad to say about the guy.
